gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 136, Raptors 130
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Raptors, 136-130. Julius Randle led the way for the Knicks with 34 points, eight rebounds and five assists, while Jalen Brunson added 21 points and a season-high nine assists in the victory. OG Anunoby tallied 29 points and five 3PM for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Knicks improve to 13-9 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 9-14.
